            <title>[GROOVY-2417] &apos;null&apos; value for a property breaks ConfigSlurper</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/GROOVY-2417</link>
                <project id="12318123" key="GROOVY">Groovy</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;If a config file sets a property to &lt;tt&gt;null&lt;/tt&gt;, the &lt;tt&gt;ConfigSlurper&lt;/tt&gt; throws NPEs when retrieving the property value and when doing &lt;tt&gt;getProperties()&lt;/tt&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I have attached a patch to the unit test for &lt;tt&gt;ConfigSlurper&lt;/tt&gt;. It should be applied from the &lt;tt&gt;groovy-core&lt;/tt&gt; directory.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
